  "summary": {
    "macroSummary": "US-Iran ceasefire agreement triggers classic risk-on rotation with oil crashing below $100, dollar weakening sharply, and safe havens like gold paradoxically rallying alongside risk assets. The two-week ceasefire timeline creates temporary relief but maintains underlying volatility structure as markets position for potential resumption of tensions.",
    "regimeImpact": "Relief rally gains momentum as oil below $100 removes immediate stagflation threat, but bear market structure remains intact given temporary nature of ceasefire and upcoming Apr 2 tariff deadline.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Accelerate BMNR cash-secured put ladder strikes as BTC reclaims $72K well above $62.3K structural level with ETH breaking $2.5K resistance",
      "Reduce short book exposure on oversold relief rally strength, particularly in oil-sensitive sectors benefiting from energy price collapse",
      "Maintain Maturity sector overweight but hedge duration risk as bond rally on ceasefire could reverse quickly if tensions resurface"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Oil diving below $100 removes immediate stagflation pressure and supports risk asset rally continuation",
      "DXY weakness with yuan at 3-year highs suggests significant capital flow shifts favoring risk-on positioning",
      "BTC above $72K and ETH above $2.5K with stablecoin supply at $180B ATH indicates strong crypto momentum",
      "Two-week ceasefire timeline creates binary event risk around resumption date, maintaining elevated volatility structure"
    ]
